    "narrative": "Our premier play for April 13 is **Corbin Carroll**, who anchors the lineup with an elite 85.94 score. Facing a favorable matchup against Kremer (4.25 xERA), **Corbin Carroll** benefits from a massive 16% park boost and a +8% efficiency bump from hitting out of the #2 hole, making him our highest-upside asset for stolen bases today. We are also leaning heavily into the Kikuchi (4.34 xERA) matchup; both **Jose Caballero** (75.02) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (67.26) receive significant upgrades due to the platoon advantage and favorable wind conditions. While **Giancarlo Stanton** (67.14) is technically facing a neutral platoon against the lefty, his raw power in this park environment makes him a mandatory start as we hunt for HR and RBI volume.\n\nWe face a difficult decision at the margins, with **Max Muncy** (45.06) serving as the primary bench casualty. While **Max Muncy** benefits from a positive park factor against Eovaldi, the combination of a tough 3.17 xERA and the Optimizer's preference for the higher-floor projections of **Dalton Rushing** and **Alex Freeland** kept him out of the starting nine. Caution is advised regarding **James Wood** and **Seiya Suzuki**; both are battling sub-3.10 xERA arms (Skenes and S\u00e1nchez respectively), and their scores are suppressed by elite catchers with rapid pop-times. We will be monitoring the pending lineups for **Dalton Rushing**, **Alex Freeland**, and **Tyler Soderstrom** closely, as any shift down the order or a late scratch could necessitate a pivot to our bench depth, specifically looking for opportunities to maximize our remaining game caps.",
